# Project Structure Rules

All application code lives in `src/`.
All tests live in `tests/` and must mirror the `src/` structure exactly.
Never create files outside these directories without explicit instruction.

Required top-level structure:
- src/         → all application code
- tests/       → mirrors src/ exactly
- docs/        → markdown documentation only
- .github/     → CI and issue templates
- docker/      → Dockerfiles and Compose files
- scripts/     → setup, healthcheck, dev utilities

Never create nested `src/src/` or `tests/tests/` structures.
Never place test files inside `src/`.
